      • patch

        void patch(java.lang.String domainId,
           java.lang.String securityPolicyId,
           java.lang.String ruleId,
           Rule rule)
        Patch the rule. If Rule corresponding to the the given rule-id is not present, the object will get created and if it is present it will be updated. This is a full replace. Performance Note: If you want to edit several rules in a security policy, prefer below mentioned API for optimal performance. Pass all the rules which you wish to edit as embedded rules to it. Use this API - PATCH (or PUT) /infra/domains//security-policies/

Performance Note: If you wish to edit several rules in a security policy, prefer below mentioned API for optimal performance. Pass all the rules which you wish to edit as embedded rules to it.
